headshotImage.caption: Shubman Gill player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shubman Gill player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: ohhhh, and he strikes first ball with an absolute beaut! A bit of flight, and the angle is bringing the ball in towards middle stump. Then it dips on Gill as he comes forward looking for a clip to mid-on, and suddenly he's nowhere near the pitch of the ball. Loses his balance as he reaches out for it, and the ball turns past his outside edge to knock back off stump

headshotImage.caption: V Kohli headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: V Kohli headshot

headshotImage.caption: RA Jadeja headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: RA Jadeja headshot

dismissalComment.html: wow, that's quick turn, and the finger is up immediately! Flat length ball, pitching just inside the line of the stumps, and turning and bouncing sharply. Jadeja is looking to work this leg side, from the crease, and the ball brushes the shoulder of his bat and nestles in Mendis's gloves

headshotImage.caption: Jasprit Bumrah player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jasprit Bumrah player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Asalanka gets his third! Dangled up nicely outside off, and Bumrah looks to work it with the turn. Lets his hands get away from his body, and the ball turns sharply between bat and pad to rattle his stumps

headshotImage.caption: Kuldeep Yadav player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kuldeep Yadav player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: and it goes straight into that fielder's hands!!! Asalanka is turning it on here. Quick, back of a length, goes back to punch into the covers, but it turns and takes his edge. Goes quickly to Dhananjaya's left at slip and he makes a good catch look simple, great footwork to get into position to pouch it with two hands, at chest height

commentPostTextItems.html: And with that, it's a wrap from us. Join us again on Thursday for Pakistan v Sri Lanka, which will be a virtual semi-final. But for now, on behalf of Karthik and the team, this is Madushka saying goodnight!
Indian_Pus: "Why did the other Sri Lankan batters get out so easily? Because they thought they had Dunith (done it)" --- Great pun to end the night on.
Adi: "Wellalage => He is definitely captain material in the future. Amazing maturity he is showing. Congratulating India when asked a question about his performance. "
Mukesh : "Wellalage, such a composer during his interview. Salute from Indians!!"

Player of the Match goes to Dunith Wellalage for figures of 5 for 40 with the ball and an unbeaten 46-ball 42: "First of all I want to congratulate the Indian team. Unfortunately we lost the match today, but we have one more game to make it to the final. Kuldeep Yadav is a great bowler, but I tried to play my normal game and stay positive. [How were you feeling?] Since a small age I worked hard, had a positive mindset. Want to thank my teammates and supporting staff."

Indian skipper Rohit Sharma gets an award for the most sixes: "It was a good game. For us also to play a game like that under pressure. Challenged a lot of aspects of our game. We definitely want to play on pitches like to see what we can achieve. [Hardik] He's worked hard on his bowling over the last couple of years, and it's pleasing to see how he bowled that spell. Not an easy target to defend. Pitch got slightly better towards the end so we had to hold our nerve and bowl consistently. [Kuldeep?] Again for the past year or so bowling really well. He's worked hard on his rhythm and you can see the results in the last 15 ODIs he's played. He gives us a lot of options. So going forward it's a pretty good sign."
Surya Kumar Yadav takes the award for Catch of the Match

This is the points table as things stand. Sri Lanka still has a superior net run rate than Pakistan, what that means is that only a win will do for Pakistan on Thursday. A washout means Sri Lanka will make the final.
Stay tuned, we'll have the post-match presentation in a bit
Azweer : "Kuldeep completes 150 ODI wickets..." --- This went under the radar, but a great spell well capped off.
Saksham: "Like common sense prevailed with the shortened innings break, hopefully they maintain consistency by giving Dunith the POTM award even though he ended up on the losing side."
Prashantha: "Dunith Wellalage a Star is born!!"

Dasun Shanaka: "We didn't expect this kind of a wicket, but after the first 10 overs we came into the match brilliantly with the spinners. The luxury of the two genuine batters bowling is great, they've done well in the nets but it was great how they performed. [Wellalage?] After the last game with Bangladesh I sensed he would do something special."

But despite the result, this was a day that belonged to Dunith Wellalage. With the ball he grabbed a five-for, and with the bat he nearly stole the win for his side. He also took an excellent catch to complete a tremendous all-round performance.

10.56pm So India too good for Sri Lanka in the end, in what turned out to be quite the low-scoring thriller. The margin of victory doesn't tell the whole story, not by a long shot, as Sri Lanka had India genuinely worried when Wellalage and Dhananjaya were going strong in their 63-run 7th wicket stand. But once the latter fell, the tail just couldn't hang on, on what was a difficult surface at the Premadasa and Kuldeep came in to clean house.
